CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 5, 1960, pg. A15, reads: "Discussing 'Y' Strategy -"Discussing 'Y' Strategy - ... The Centre Avenue branch's 1960 enrollment workers have produced 830 members to date.  The branch has reached 89 per cent of its goal.  The workers will be rounding up 120 former members whose names till be recorded at homecoming members in observance of the 50th year of the Centre Avenue branch.  To be a homecoming member, your membership must be reported on Monday night, March 7, by and enrolment worker. - Harris Photo."Names on chart in background include: Thomas Sumpter, Raymond Boer.
TitMainTitle: Thomas J. "Tommy" Smith, Mrs. Jones wearing lei, and Paul F. Jones, standing in front of tote board for Centre Avenue Branch YMCA 1960 membership campaign
